      <preamble>
         <formula name="enactingText">
            <p>The Scottish Ministers make the following Regulations in exercise of the powers conferred by paragraph 1(1) and (3) of schedule 2 of the European Union (Withdrawal) Act 2018<noteRef href="#f00001" class="footnote" marker="1"/> and all other powers enabling them to do so.</p>
         </formula>
      </preamble>
      <body>
         <hcontainer name="regulation" eId="regulation-1">
            <heading>Citation and commencement</heading>
            <num>1.</num>
            <content>
               <p>These Regulations may be cited as the Wildlife and Countryside Act 1981 (EU Exit) (Scotland) (Amendment) Regulations 2019 and come into force on exit day.</p>
            </content>
         </hcontainer>
         <hcontainer name="regulation" eId="regulation-2">
            <heading>Amendment of the Wildlife and Countryside Act 1981</heading>
            <num>2.</num>
            <content>
               <p>In section 27(1) of the Wildlife and Countryside Act 1981<noteRef href="#f00002" class="footnote" marker="2"/>, in the definition of “wild bird”, after “visitor to” insert “the United Kingdom or”.</p>
            </content>
         </hcontainer>
